definitions.definition: A flexible enclosing or separating tissue forming a plane or film and separating two environments .

subdefinitions.definition: A mechanical , thin, flat flexible part that can deform or vibrate when excited by an external force .
A flexible or semiflexible covering or waterproofing whose primary function is to exclude water.
A microscopic double layer of lipids and proteins forming the boundary of cells or organelles .

definitions.definition: A piece of parchment forming part of a roll .

main_definition: ( anatomy , zootomy ) A flexible enclosing or separating tissue forming a plane or film and separating two environments .
secondary_definitions: A piece of parchment forming part of a roll .
